SIMPLE: catadromous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catadromous
<hw>Ca*tad"ro*mous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kata`</grk> down + <grk>dro`mos</grk> a running.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the lowest inferior segment of a pinna
nearer the rachis than the lowest superior one; -- said of a mode of
branching in ferns, and opposed to <contr>anadromous</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Living in fresh water, and going
to the sea to spawn; -- opposed to <contr>anadromous</contr>, and said
of the eel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catafalco</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
